msgid "VR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:452
msgid ""
"**`vtkOpenXRManager::Initialize` and `vtkOpenXRManager::Finalize` marked as "
"internal APIs**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:454
msgid ""
"These functions are now treated as internal to `vtkOpenXRRenderWindow`. The "
"signature of `vtkOpenXRManager::Initialize` has changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:456
msgid ""
"**`vtkOpenXRManager::(Set|Get)UseDepthExtension` moved to "
"`vtkOpenXRRenderWindow`**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:458
msgid ""
"These methods have been moved to `vtkOpenXRRenderWindow`. The "
"`vtkOpenXRManager` versions are now no-op and deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:462
msgid "**Change Java build flags**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:464
msgid ""
"`VTK_JAVA_SOURCE_VERSION` and `VTK_JAVA_TARGET_VERSION` CMake flags are "
"superseded by `VTK_JAVA_RELEASE_VERSION`. This aligns with newer JDK `javac` "
"versions that provide the `-release` flag, simplifying build configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:466
msgid "Fixes/improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:468
msgid "Charts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:470
msgid "**Fix vtkPlotBar::GetBounds logic when log scale is enabled**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:472
msgid ""
"The `vtkPlotBar::GetBounds(double*, bool unscaled)` now correctly returns "
"unscaled bounds when `unscaled` is true and scaled bounds when `unscaled` is "
"false."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:476
msgid "**Fix CellTreeLocator for 2D grids**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:478
msgid ""
"A `std::vector` out of bounds access has been fixed when building the "
"locator for meshes whose x, y or z extent is zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:480
msgid "**Polygon centroid computation fixed**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:482
msgid ""
"An issue with `vtkPolygon::ComputeCentroid()` has been fixed. It now uses a "
"composite weighted-area triangulation for robustness with non-planar "
"polygons and includes a planarity tolerance.   ([Author notes](9.5/fix-"
"polygon-centroid.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:485
msgid ""
"**vtkPolyhedron: Implement GetCentroid and use it in GetParametricCenter**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:487
msgid ""
"In VTK 9.5.1, the `vtkPolyhedron` class introduces the `GetCentroid` "
"function, which computes the signed-volume weighted centroid of a polyhedron "
"using its pyramid decomposition. The `GetParametricCenter` method has been "
"updated to return the parametric location of the centroid returned from "
"`vtkPolyhedron`'s `GetCentroid` function.   ([Author notes](9.5/fix-"
"polyhedron-parametric-center.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:490
msgid "**Implicit Widget Representations Improvements**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:492
msgid ""
"Improved interaction and intuitiveness in VTK's implicit widget "
"representations, including enhanced picking and mouse-based control for "
"shape sizing. A new `vtkBoundedWidgetRepresentation` base class introduces "
"cropping to outline bounds, with API changes affecting several subclasses.   "
"([Author notes](9.5/widget-representations-improvements.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:497
msgid "**Fix vtkBandedPolyDataContourFilter scalars**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:499
msgid ""
"You can now select scalars used by `vtkBandedPolyDataContourFilter` using "
"the `SetInputArrayToProcess` method instead of changing the scalars on the "
"input data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:501
msgid "**Fix vtkParticleTracer with unstructured data**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:503
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue leading to a crash in `vtkParticleTracer` where locators for "
"unstructured data would not have been created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:505
msgid "**Fix UMR in vtkDataSetTriangleFilter**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:507
msgid ""
"For a `vtkUnstructuredGrid` input consisting of only tetrahedrons, "
"`vtkDataSetTriangleFilter` could give non-deterministic results due to an "
"uninitialized memory read (UMR)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:509
msgid "**Support Partitioned Input in HyperTreeGridGhostCellsGenerator**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:511
msgid ""
"The HTG GhostCellsGenerator now natively supports Partitioned inputs, using "
"the first non-null partition found as the HTG to process, fixing issues with "
"multi-partition data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:513
msgid "**vtkGeometryFilter: Improve performance for polyhedron**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:515
msgid ""
"`vtkGeometryFilter` now efficiently extracts polyhedron faces using "
"`GetPolyhedronFaces` and `GetPolyhedronFaceLocations` methods, improving "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:517
msgid "**vtkRandomAttributesFilter: Prevent deletion of actives attributes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:519
msgid ""
"When using `vtkRandomAttributesGenerator`, the filter no longer replaces "
"active attributes; it now appends the new random array and flags it as "
"active. Random normals and tcoords are now correctly named."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:521
msgid ""
"**Relative Mode for vtkTemporalArrayOperatorFilter** :warning: "
"**BREAKING_CHANGES**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:523
msgid ""
"`vtkTemporalArrayOperatorFilter` now supports a `RelativeMode` that uses the "
"current `UPDATE_TIME_STEP` and a shifted time step for temporal operations. "
"This introduces consistent output behavior across data types and enforces "
"encapsulation via getter/setter access to formerly protected members.   "
"([Author notes](9.5/relative-temporal-array-operator.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:529
msgid "**EnsightCombinedReader: Performance improvements pass**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:531
msgid ""
"Performance of `vtkEnSightGoldCombinedReader` improved, especially for large "
"binary files with nfaced/tetrahedron cells. Fixes include tetrahedron-"
"specific cell building, block reading of connectivity data, faster parsing "
"during RequestInfo, and an int overflow fix.   ([Author notes](9.5/ensight-"
"reader-improvements.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:534
msgid "**Fix AMReX particle reader for files without top-level header**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:536
msgid ""
"The `vtkAMReXParticlesReader` now continues to read particles if a top-level "
"header is missing, initializing the time step to 0 in such cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:538
msgid "**Fix ordering of DICOM pixel spacing**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:540
msgid ""
"The `vtkDICOMImageReader` used to provide the vertical and horizontal pixel "
"spacing in the wrong order. This issue was only discovered recently because "
"DICOM pixels are nearly always square."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:542
msgid "**Fix issue with Fides not initializing HIP before using it**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:544
msgid ""
"Addressed a crash in Fides caused by attempting HIP memory allocation before "
"HIP initialization. This was fixed by updating VTK-m.   ([Author notes](9.5/"
"fides-init.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:547
msgid ""
"**Fix vtkAMReXGridReader when reading larger than 2GB files in Windows**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:549
msgid ""
"You can now open grid files larger than 2GB on Windows using the "
"`vtkAMReXGridReader`. Previously, a bug prevented loading arrays stored "
"beyond the 2GB offset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:551
msgid "**Fix vtkAMReXParticlesReader when using MPI**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:553
msgid ""
"The `vtkAMReXParticlesReader` now functions correctly in parallel MPI mode, "
"fixing a bug that caused incorrect output when the number of grids was not "
"evenly divisible by the number of MPI processes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:555
msgid "**GLTF document loader default scene**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:557
msgid ""
"The `vtkGLTFDocumentLoader` ensures that the internal cache of scenes is non-"
"empty for consumer code that relies on checking the validity of the default "
"scene."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:559
msgid "**Remove error for missing Fides timestep**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:561
msgid ""
"The Fides reader no longer errors if a requested timestep is not found, "
"especially when the Fides file has no specified timesteps. It now sets an "
"appropriate time index (0) in such cases, improving compatibility with tools "
"like ParaView.   ([Author notes](9.5/fides-timestep-error.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:564
msgid ""
"**vtkDIYGhostUtilities: Ensure arrays are enqueued and dequeued properly**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:566
msgid ""
"Improvements to `vtkDIYUtilities` and `vtkDIYGhostUtilities` for stricter "
"loading, correct saving of array types, ensuring dequeued arrays are valid, "
"and fixing polyhedral meshes in `vtkConduitToDataObject`.   ([Author notes]"
"(9.5/fix-ghost-cells-polyhedrons.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:569
msgid "**vtkAlembicExporter: Fixed export of textures**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:571
msgid ""
"Previously, textures were unintentionally being saved to the current working "
"directory of the executable. Now, they are saved alongside the exported "
"Alembic file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:573
msgid "**VRML export of cell data colors**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:575
msgid ""
"Colors of polydata colored by cell data arrays are now designated as such in "
"the exported VRML file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:577
msgid "MPI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:579
msgid "**Fix: MPI Gather function hanging when data size was invalid**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:581
msgid ""
"`vtkMPICommunicator::GatherVVoidArray` could hang due to a size check "
"causing an early return for only the failing process. Now, `recvLengths` and "
"`offsets` must be specified for all processes when calling `vtkCommunicator::"
"GatherV` to prevent this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:585
msgid "**Python VTK data model improvements**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:587
msgid ""
"Further cleaned up field array handling in Python for homogeneous behavior "
"between `vtkDataSet` and composite datasets. This includes better support "
"for dictionary-like access to `point_data` and `cell_data`.   ([Author notes]"
"(9.5/fix-py-data-model.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:592
msgid "**ANARI renderer warnings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:594
msgid ""
"The ANARI scenegraph implementation has been fixed so that missing backend "
"feature warnings are only issued once per renderer per device, reducing "
"output buffer spam. Various compiler warnings in ANARI integration classes "
"have also been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:596
msgid "**Fix actor lighting flag for WASM and cell grid rendering**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:598
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug that caused an actor to disappear when lighting was disabled on "
"an actor in WASM with the WebGL2 backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:600
msgid "**Fix wide line rendering in GLES default polydata mapper**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:602
msgid ""
"The `vtkOpenGLLowMemoryPolyDataMapper` rendered thick lines incorrectly. It "
"appeared as an extruded cross. This issue is now fixed in the mapper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:604
msgid "**Fix lighting calculations for PBR interpolation**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:606
msgid ""
"![](https://vtk.org/files/ExternalData/"
"SHA512/01b2f3261b9dc1550b1dae1abcc32ab45c170964500115ee66efba9200ff46485d2bee6efe1e13c6972630661c29dfac5abc83de7ac88b21d566a3db215936d4)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:608
msgid ""
"When both directional and positional lights were intermixed, the polydata "
"mapper treated directional lights as positional, generating incorrect "
"renderings. This is now fixed.   ([Author notes](https://gitlab.kitware.com/"
"vtk/vtk/-/tree/master/Documentation/release/9.5/pbr-lighting.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:611
msgid ""
"**Fix low memory polydata mapper when an actor is added after another is "
"removed from a renderer**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:613
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in `vtkOpenGLLowMemoryPolyDataMapper` where an actor, if added, "
"removed, and then re-added, would not become visible the second time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:615
msgid "**Fix OpenGL error in OSMesa backend**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:617
msgid ""
"Fixed a `GL_INVALID_ENUM` error in `vtkOSOpenGLRenderWindow::"
"ReportCapabilities` caused by using an unsupported method for querying "
"`GL_EXTENSIONS`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:619
msgid "**Fix vtkCompositePolyDataMapper opacity override**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:621
msgid "![](imgs/9.5/fix-composite-mapper-opacity-override.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:623
msgid ""
"You can now render opaque blocks in a composite dataset even when the actor "
"has an `opacity < 1.0` by setting the opacity of the block to 1.0.   "
"([Author notes](9.5/fix-composite-mapper-opacity-override.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:626
msgid "**Fix vertex visibility in OpenGL mappers**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:628
msgid ""
"Vertices of a mesh are now correctly displayed when `actor-"
">SetVertexVisibility(true)` is called, fixing a bug where they only showed "
"if edge visibility was also on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:630
msgid "**Fix wide lines with cell colors for Apple silicon**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:632
msgid ""
"Thick lines with cell scalar colors now render correctly on Apple silicon. "
"VTK patches the shader code at runtime for the Apple OpenGL over Metal "
"driver to handle an upstream bug. Use `vtkOpenGLRenderWindow::"
"IsPrimIDBugPresent()` to check for this driver bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:634
msgid "**Improve IBO construction performances in vtkOpenGLIndexBufferObject**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:636
msgid ""
"For common cases of triangles-only polydata, IBO construction time has been "
"reduced by about 25%. Performance is further improved if polydata cell "
"arrays use 32-bit connectivity IDs.   ([Author notes](9.5/index-buffer-"
"creation-performances.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:639
msgid "**Rectilinear Grid Volume Rendering with Cell Data**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:641
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue in the volume mapper for rectilinear grids with cell scalars "
"where the bounds of the dataset were incorrectly mapped to the texture space."
msgstr ""

