#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:647
msgid "**Fix X error about maximum clients reached**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:649
msgid ""
"Fixes a bug in `vtkXOpenGLRenderWindow` that prevented users from "
"instantiating more than about 300 render windows on Linux with X11."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:651
msgid "**Fix light transforms when computing shadow maps**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:653
msgid ""
"The `vtkShadowMapBakerPass` computes shadow maps for each light by "
"simulating a `vtkCamera` for each light and compositing the rendered images. "
"However, an unintentional side-effect of this was that the original light's "
"transforms were being affected by this. In other words, the lights would be "
"corrupt after the shadow map computation. To circumvent this, we cache the "
"light transforms prior to the shadow map computation and then reset them "
"after."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:655
msgid ""
"![](http://vtk.org/files/ExternalData/"
"SHA512/9412ed54080c7a972d786a269538a3dbd56a5aa070f2b35ba448dfd3cca211e7e4b4d196e07c8ff2d56ff4bb7b0855e5584758c09457d3d6f3c760ee47a4dded)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:659
msgid ""
"**Patch state that refers to OSMesa OpenGL window into a WASM OpenGL window "
"class.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:661
msgid ""
"The `vtkWasmSceneManager` now automatically patches the state provided to "
"`RegisterState` and `UpdateObjectFromState` methods to replace 'ClassName' "
"entry of `vtkOSOpenGLRenderWindow` with `vtkWebAssemblyOpenGLRenderWindow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:663
msgid "Deprecations/Removals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:665
msgid "All APIs that were deprecated in 9.3 are now removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:666
msgid ""
"`vtkExtentSplitter::Min` and `::Max` have been deprecated in favor of `std::"
"min` and `std::max`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:667
msgid ""
"`vtkXMLReader::Min` and `::Max` have been deprecated in favor of `std::min` "
"and `std::max`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:668
msgid ""
"Classes like `vtkHierarchicalBoxDataSet`, "
"`vtkHierarchicalBoxDataSetAlgorithm`, related geometry filters, and XML "
"readers/writers are deprecated. Use `vtkOverlappingAMR` versions instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:669
msgid ""
"`vtkTypedDataArray`, `vtkTypedDataArrayIterator`, `vtkMappedDataArray`, "
"`vtkCPExodusIINodalCoordinatesTemplate`, and "
"`vtkCPExodusIIResultsArrayTemplate` are deprecated. Use "
"`vtkGenericDataArray` or `vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate`/`vtkSOADataArrayTemplate` "
"alternatives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:670
msgid ""
"`vtkHyperTreeGridVisibleLeavesSize` is deprecated in favor of "
"`vtkHyperTreeGridGenerateFields`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:671
msgid ""
"Several public members related to selection and decimation level in "
"`vtkAdaptiveDataSetSurfaceFilter` (used by HTG Surface Representation) are "
"now deprecated and have no effect (e.g., `Set/GetCircleSelection`, `Set/"
"GetDynamicDecimateLevelMax`).   ([Author notes](9.5/htg-representation-"
"decimation.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:673
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenXRManager::(Set|Get)UseDepthExtension` are deprecated and now no-op. "
"Use the versions in `vtkOpenXRRenderWindow` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:675
msgid "**VTKHDF Reader: Remove the MergeParts option**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:677
msgid ""
"The `MergeParts` option of the vtkHDFReader allowed getting a unique "
"Unstructured Grid or PolyData dataset after reading multiple parts. This "
"option has been deprecated and has no effect anymore. Now, multi-piece "
"datasets properly output a vtkPartitionedDataset containing non merged "
"parts. Single-piece datasets still output simple vtkUnstructuredGrid or "
"vtkPolyData. This **changes the default behavior of the reader**: "
"Unstructured Grid and PolyData multi-piece datasets that used to be read "
"with `MergeParts` (default) as a single piece are now read as a partitioned "
"dataset. If `MergeParts` was disabled manually, only the single-piece case "
"will be read differently: instead of forcing the output to be a partitioned "
"dataset with a single piece, the output is now directly the non composite "
"type, Unstructured Grid or PolyData."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:679
msgid ""
"Users should replace the use of `MergeParts` by manually merging parts using "
"the `vtkMergeBlocks` or `vtkAppendDatasets` manually instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:681
msgid "Updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:683
msgid "The following changes have been made since v9.5.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:685
msgid "9.5.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:687
msgid "**Fix HyperTree initialization routine**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:689
msgid ""
"`vtkHyperTree::Initialize` used to incorrectly set up a internal data "
"structure, causing incorrect iterations indices for "
"`vtkHyperTreeGridNonOrientedUnlimitedSuperCursor::ToChild`. This fixes the "
"Gradient filter results using \"Unlimited\" mode for HTG, which now gives "
"correct values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:691
msgid "**Fix serialization for vtkPlane**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:693
msgid ""
"Resolved an issue with `vtkPlane` serialization where plane parameters were "
"not correctly saved and restored. This ensures consistent behavior when "
"serializing and deserializing `vtkPlane` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:695
msgid "**Fix MouseWheel events in WASM for multi-viewport setups**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.5-stripped.md:697
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where mouse wheel event coordinates were incorrectly scaled "
"in `vtkWebAssemblyRenderWindowInteractor`. When the `window."
"devicePixelRatio` value was not equal to 1 in multi-viewport setups, it "
"caused a different renderer to zoom its contents instead of the renderer "
"which was under the mouse cursor. The `ProcessEvent` method now properly "
"handles coordinate scaling for MouseWheel events, ensuring consistent zoom "
"behavior across all viewports."
msgstr ""
